  "informal_statement": "For every pair of real numbers a, b: the absolute value of |a| - |b| is at most |a - b| -- the full (doubly-absolute) reverse triangle inequality, strengthening the domain's existing one-sided reverse_triangle.v1 (|a| - |b| <= |a - b|) by also bounding the case |b| - |a| > 0.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Case-split the signs of a, b, a - b, and |a| - |b| via abs_cases (16 branches); every branch reduces to a purely linear fact about a, b and their sign-determined absolute-value expressions, closed uniformly by nlinarith given all eight case hypotheses as hints.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem abs_abs_sub_abs_le (a b : ℝ) : |(|a| - |b|)| ≤ |a - b|",
